message.content: cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.ET - This paper discusses the experience of using a verification tool to statically verify a small object-oriented program, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the methodology-related issues, which could be related to logic and computation (cs.LO) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper proposes changes to simplify the tool and method, which could be related to emerging technologies (cs.ET).
